      • associationDocumentStorage

        public MongoDBPropertyContext associationDocumentStorage(AssociationDocumentStorageType associationDocumentStorage)
        Description copied from interface: MongoDBPropertyContext
        Specifies how association documents should be persisted. Only applies when the current property represents an association and the association storage strategy is set to AssociationStorageType.ASSOCIATION_DOCUMENT.
        Specified by:
        associationDocumentStorage in interface MongoDBPropertyContext
        Parameters:
        associationDocumentStorage - the association document type to be used; overrides any settings on the entity or global level
        Returns:
        this context, allowing for further fluent API invocations

      • writeConcern

        public MongoDBPropertyContext writeConcern(com.mongodb.WriteConcern writeConcern)
        Description copied from interface: MongoDBPropertyContext
        Specifies a custom WriteConcern implementation to be applied when performing write operations in case the current property represents an association. Otherwise the setting takes no effect.

        Either use this option or MongoDBPropertyContext.writeConcern(WriteConcernType) but not both at the same type.

        Specified by:
        writeConcern in interface MongoDBPropertyContext
        Parameters:
        writeConcern - the write concern
        Returns:
        this context, allowing for further fluent API invocations
